[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm contemplating whether to include untracked metadata status, but ultimately, I decide against it. The user likely expects only the active class, and we didn't change the metadata. However, calling "JLineNativeLoader.initialize()" might start a cleanup daemon, which could keep the process alive. I also realize that dynamic access tracking may see call sites during the active class's JVM test run. There’s a possibility that loading the native library could fail due to dependencies in the GraalVM JDK. It's worth testing!
