 the same JVM. I realize the Native Image won’t allow System.load with JNI due to the included config. It seems unnecessary to modify metadata since the upstream jline jar already includes this. One test can cover all scenarios, which simplifies things!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering metadata and library loading**\\n\\nI'm contemplating whether to include untracked metadata status, but ultimately, I decide against it. The user likely expects only the active class, and we didn't change the metadata. However, calling \\\"JLineNativeLoader.initialize()\\\" might start a cleanup daemon, which could keep the process alive. I also realize that dynamic access tracking may see call sites during the active class's JVM test run. There’s a possibility that loading the native library could fail due to dependencies in the GraalVM JDK. It's worth testing!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `org.jline.nativ.JLineNativeLoader`.\n\nChanges:\n- Added `tests/src/org.jline/jline-native/3.27.1/src/test/java/org_jline/jline_native/JLineNativeLoaderTest.java`\n  - Calls public `JLineNativeLoader.initialize()`\n  - Forces bundled-resource loading by clearing `library.jline.path` and `library.jline.name`\n  - Asserts the extracted native library path exists\n  - Asserts the source URL comes from the bundled `org/jline/nativ` resource\n- Removed the scaffold-only placeholder test `Jline_nativeTest.java`\n\nThis should exercise:\n- `hasResource(...)`\n- both `getResourceAsStream(...)` extraction paths\n- `getResource(...)` for the loaded native library source URL\n\nI did not run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0756f404e31947770169f744ce10e8819fb4f3024b020b75c3\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 556, "output": 695, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22755, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead"